Before you start, make sure to disconnect your MicroView from your computer’s USB Port.

For this circuit you will
need a piezo element.
Insert your MicroView and Programmer with Pin 1 in hole C9.
Select your piezo element and insert it into points D18 and D21 of your breadboard.
Select your black wire and insert it into points A16 and A18 of your breadboard.
Select your red wire and insert it into points A12 and A21 of your breadboard.
Connect your MicroView to your computer’s USB Port.
Swipe Left to go to the next page
Swipe Right to go back to the previous page
If you have a keyboard you can also use the arrow keys
